  208. void make_window8(unsigned char *buf, int xsize, int ysize, char *title)
  209. {
  210. 	static char closebtn[14][16] = {
  211. 		"OOOOOOOOOOOOOOO@",
  212. 		"OQQQQQQQQQQQQQ$@",
  213. 		"OQQQQQQQQQQQQQ$@",
  214. 		"OQQQ@@QQQQ@@QQ$@",
  215. 		"OQQQQ@@QQ@@QQQ$@",
  216. 		"OQQQQQ@@@@QQQQ$@",
  217. 		"OQQQQQQ@@QQQQQ$@",
  218. 		"OQQQQQ@@@@QQQQ$@",
  219. 		"OQQQQ@@QQ@@QQQ$@",
  220. 		"OQQQ@@QQQQ@@QQ$@",
  221. 		"OQQQQQQQQQQQQQ$@",
  222. 		"OQQQQQQQQQQQQQ$@",
  223. 		"O$$$$$$$$$$$$$$@",
  224. 		"@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@"
  225. 	};
  226. 	int x, y;
  227. 	char c;
  228. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_C6C6C6, 0,         0,         xsize - 1, 0        );
  229. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_FFFFFF, 1,         1,         xsize - 2, 1        );
  230. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_C6C6C6, 0,         0,         0,         ysize - 1);
  231. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_FFFFFF, 1,         1,         1,         ysize - 2);
  232. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_848484, xsize - 2, 1,         xsize - 2, ysize - 2);
  233. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_000000, xsize - 1, 0,         xsize - 1, ysize - 1);
  234. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_C6C6C6, 2,         2,         xsize - 3, ysize - 3);
  235. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_000084, 3,         3,         xsize - 4, 20       );
  236. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_848484, 1,         ysize - 2, xsize - 2, ysize - 2);
  237. 	boxfill8(buf, xsize, COL8_000000, 0,         ysize - 1, xsize - 1, ysize - 1);
  238. 	putfonts8_asc(buf, xsize, 24, 4, COL8_FFFFFF, title);
  239. 	for (y = 0; y < 14; y++) {
  240. 		for (x = 0; x < 16; x++) {
  241. 			c = closebtn[y][x];
  242. 			if (c == '@') {
  243. 				c = COL8_000000;
  244. 			} else if (c == '$') {
  245. 				c = COL8_848484;
  246. 			} else if (c == 'Q') {
  247. 				c = COL8_C6C6C6;
  248. 			} else {
  249. 				c = COL8_FFFFFF;
  250. 			}
  251. 			buf[(5 + y) * xsize + (xsize - 21 + x)] = c;
  252. 		}
  253. 	}
  254. 	return;
  255. }

  265. void make_textbox8(struct SHEET *sht, int x0, int y0, int sx, int sy, int c)
  266. {
  267. 	int x1 = x0 + sx, y1 = y0 + sy;
  268. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_848484, x0 - 2, y0 - 3, x1 + 1, y0 - 3);
  269. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_848484, x0 - 3, y0 - 3, x0 - 3, y1 + 1);
  270. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_FFFFFF, x0 - 3, y1 + 2, x1 + 1, y1 + 2);
  271. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_FFFFFF, x1 + 2, y0 - 3, x1 + 2, y1 + 2);
  272. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_000000, x0 - 1, y0 - 2, x1 + 0, y0 - 2);
  273. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_000000, x0 - 2, y0 - 2, x0 - 2, y1 + 0);
  274. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_C6C6C6, x0 - 2, y1 + 1, x1 + 0, y1 + 1);
  275. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, COL8_C6C6C6, x1 + 1, y0 - 2, x1 + 1, y1 + 1);
  276. 	boxfill8(sht->buf, sht->bxsize, c, x0 - 1, y0 - 1, x1 + 0, y1 + 0);
  277. 	return;
  278. }
  279.  
  280. void task_b_main(struct SHEET *sht_back)
  281. {
  282. 	struct FIFO32 fifo;
  283. 	struct TIMER *timer_put, *timer_1s;
  284. 	int i, fifobuf[128], count = 0, count0 = 0;
  285. 	char s[12];
  286.  
  287. 	fifo32_init(&fifo, 128, fifobuf);
  288. 	timer_put = timer_alloc();
  289. 	timer_init(timer_put, &fifo, 1);
  290. 	timer_settime(timer_put, 1);
  291. 	timer_1s = timer_alloc();
  292. 	timer_init(timer_1s, &fifo, 100);
  293. 	timer_settime(timer_1s, 100);
  294.  
  295. 	for (;;) {
  296. 		count++;
  297. 		io_cli();
  298. 		if (fifo32_status(&fifo) == 0) {
  299. 			io_sti();
  300. 		} else {
  301. 			i = fifo32_get(&fifo);
  302. 			io_sti();
  303. 			if (i == 1) {
  304. 				sprintf(s, "%11d", count);
  305. 				putfonts8_asc_sht(sht_back, 0, 144, COL8_FFFFFF, COL8_008484, s, 11);
  306. 				timer_settime(timer_put, 1);
  307. 			} else if (i == 100) {
  308. 				sprintf(s, "%11d", count - count0);
  309. 				putfonts8_asc_sht(sht_back, 0, 128, COL8_FFFFFF, COL8_008484, s, 11);
  310. 				count0 = count;
  311. 				timer_settime(timer_1s, 100);
  312. 			}
  313. 		}
  314. 	}
  315. }

mtask.c:

  1. /* 多任务管理 */
  2.  
  3. #include "bootpack.h"
  4.  
  5. struct TIMER *mt_timer;
  6. int mt_tr;
  7.  
  8. void mt_init(void)
  9. {
  10. 	mt_timer = timer_alloc();
  11. 	/*这里没有必要使用timer_init */
  12. 	timer_settime(mt_timer, 2);
  13. 	mt_tr = 3 * 8;
  14. 	return;
  15. }
  16.  
  17. void mt_taskswitch(void)
  18. {
  19. 	if (mt_tr == 3 * 8) {
  20. 		mt_tr = 4 * 8;
  21. 	} else {
  22. 		mt_tr = 3 * 8;
  23. 	}
  24. 	timer_settime(mt_timer, 2);
  25. 	farjmp(0, mt_tr);
  26. 	return;
  27. }

  6. [BITS 32]						; 3制作32位模式用的机器语言
  7. [FILE "naskfunc.nas"]			; 文件名
  8.  
  9. 		GLOBAL	_io_hlt, _io_cli, _io_sti, _io_stihlt
  10. 		GLOBAL	_io_in8,  _io_in16,  _io_in32
  11. 		GLOBAL	_io_out8, _io_out16, _io_out32
  12. 		GLOBAL	_io_load_eflags, _io_store_eflags
  13. 		GLOBAL	_load_gdtr, _load_idtr
  14. 		GLOBAL	_load_cr0, _store_cr0
  15. 		GLOBAL	_load_tr
  16. 		GLOBAL	_asm_inthandler20, _asm_inthandler21
  17. 		GLOBAL	_asm_inthandler27, _asm_inthandler2c
  18. 		GLOBAL	_memtest_sub
  19. 		GLOBAL	_farjmp
  20. 		EXTERN	_inthandler20, _inthandler21
  21. 		EXTERN	_inthandler27, _inthandler2c
  22.  
  23. [SECTION .text]
  24.  
  25. _io_hlt:	; void io_hlt(void);
  26. 		HLT
  27. 		RET
  28.  
  29. _io_cli:	; void io_cli(void);
  30. 		CLI
  31. 		RET
  32.  
  33. _io_sti:	; void io_sti(void);
  34. 		STI
  35. 		RET
  36.  
  37. _io_stihlt:	; void io_stihlt(void);
  38. 		STI
  39. 		HLT
  40. 		RET
  41.  
  42. _io_in8:	; int io_in8(int port);
  43. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  44. 		MOV		EAX,0
  45. 		IN		AL,DX
  46. 		RET
  47.  
  48. _io_in16:	; int io_in16(int port);
  49. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  50. 		MOV		EAX,0
  51. 		IN		AX,DX
  52. 		RET
  53.  
  54. _io_in32:	; int io_in32(int port);
  55. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  56. 		IN		EAX,DX
  57. 		RET
  58.  
  59. _io_out8:	; void io_out8(int port, int data);
  60. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  61. 		MOV		AL,[ESP+8]		; data
  62. 		OUT		DX,AL
  63. 		RET
  64.  
  65. _io_out16:	; void io_out16(int port, int data);
  66. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  67. 		MOV		EAX,[ESP+8]		; data
  68. 		OUT		DX,AX
  69. 		RET
  70.  
  71. _io_out32:	; void io_out32(int port, int data);
  72. 		MOV		EDX,[ESP+4]		; port
  73. 		MOV		EAX,[ESP+8]		; data
  74. 		OUT		DX,EAX
  75. 		RET
  76.  
  77. _io_load_eflags:	; int io_load_eflags(void);
  78. 		PUSHFD		; PUSH EFLAGS 
  79. 		POP		EAX
  80. 		RET
  81.  
  82. _io_store_eflags:	; void io_store_eflags(int eflags);
  83. 		MOV		EAX,[ESP+4]
  84. 		PUSH	EAX
  85. 		POPFD		; POP EFLAGS 
  86. 		RET
  87.  
  88. _load_gdtr:		; void load_gdtr(int limit, int addr);
  89. 		MOV		AX,[ESP+4]		; limit
  90. 		MOV		[ESP+6],AX
  91. 		LGDT	[ESP+6]
  92. 		RET
  93.  
  94. _load_idtr:		; void load_idtr(int limit, int addr);
  95. 		MOV		AX,[ESP+4]		; limit
  96. 		MOV		[ESP+6],AX
  97. 		LIDT	[ESP+6]
  98. 		RET
  99.  
  100. _load_cr0:		; int load_cr0(void);
  101. 		MOV		EAX,CR0
  102. 		RET
  103.  
  104. _store_cr0:		; void store_cr0(int cr0);
  105. 		MOV		EAX,[ESP+4]
  106. 		MOV		CR0,EAX
  107. 		RET
  108.  
  109. _load_tr:		; void load_tr(int tr);
  110. 		LTR		[ESP+4]			; tr
  111. 		RET
  112.  
  113. _asm_inthandler20:
  114. 		PUSH	ES
  115. 		PUSH	DS
  116. 		PUSHAD
  117. 		MOV		EAX,ESP
  118. 		PUSH	EAX
  119. 		MOV		AX,SS
  120. 		MOV		DS,AX
  121. 		MOV		ES,AX
  122. 		CALL	_inthandler20
  123. 		POP		EAX
  124. 		POPAD
  125. 		POP		DS
  126. 		POP		ES
  127. 		IRETD
  128.  
  129. _asm_inthandler21:
  130. 		PUSH	ES
  131. 		PUSH	DS
  132. 		PUSHAD
  133. 		MOV		EAX,ESP
  134. 		PUSH	EAX
  135. 		MOV		AX,SS
  136. 		MOV		DS,AX
  137. 		MOV		ES,AX
  138. 		CALL	_inthandler21
  139. 		POP		EAX
  140. 		POPAD
  141. 		POP		DS
  142. 		POP		ES
  143. 		IRETD
  144.  
  145. _asm_inthandler27:
  146. 		PUSH	ES
  147. 		PUSH	DS
  148. 		PUSHAD
  149. 		MOV		EAX,ESP
  150. 		PUSH	EAX
  151. 		MOV		AX,SS
  152. 		MOV		DS,AX
  153. 		MOV		ES,AX
  154. 		CALL	_inthandler27
  155. 		POP		EAX
  156. 		POPAD
  157. 		POP		DS
  158. 		POP		ES
  159. 		IRETD
  160.  
  161. _asm_inthandler2c:
  162. 		PUSH	ES
  163. 		PUSH	DS
  164. 		PUSHAD
  165. 		MOV		EAX,ESP
  166. 		PUSH	EAX
  167. 		MOV		AX,SS
  168. 		MOV		DS,AX
  169. 		MOV		ES,AX
  170. 		CALL	_inthandler2c
  171. 		POP		EAX
  172. 		POPAD
  173. 		POP		DS
  174. 		POP		ES
  175. 		IRETD
  176.  
  177. _memtest_sub:	; unsigned int memtest_sub(unsigned int start, unsigned int end)
  178. 		PUSH	EDI						; （由于还要使用EBX, ESI, EDI）
  179. 		PUSH	ESI
  180. 		PUSH	EBX
  181. 		MOV		ESI,0xaa55aa55			; pat0 = 0xaa55aa55;
  182. 		MOV		EDI,0x55aa55aa			; pat1 = 0x55aa55aa;
  183. 		MOV		EAX,[ESP+12+4]			; i = start;
  184. mts_loop:
  185. 		MOV		EBX,EAX
  186. 		ADD		EBX,0xffc				; p = i + 0xffc;
  187. 		MOV		EDX,[EBX]				; old = *p;
  188. 		MOV		[EBX],ESI				; *p = pat0;
  189. 		XOR		DWORD [EBX],0xffffffff	; *p ^= 0xffffffff;
  190. 		CMP		EDI,[EBX]				; if (*p != pat1) goto fin;
  191. 		JNE		mts_fin
  192. 		XOR		DWORD [EBX],0xffffffff	; *p ^= 0xffffffff;
  193. 		CMP		ESI,[EBX]				; if (*p != pat0) goto fin;
  194. 		JNE		mts_fin
  195. 		MOV		[EBX],EDX				; *p = old;
  196. 		ADD		EAX,0x1000				; i += 0x1000;
  197. 		CMP		EAX,[ESP+12+8]			; if (i <= end) goto mts_loop;
  198. 		JBE		mts_loop
  199. 		POP		EBX
  200. 		POP		ESI
  201. 		POP		EDI
  202. 		RET
  203. mts_fin:
  204. 		MOV		[EBX],EDX				; *p = old;
  205. 		POP		EBX
  206. 		POP		ESI
  207. 		POP		EDI
  208. 		RET
  209.  
  210. _farjmp:		; void farjmp(int eip, int cs);
  211. 		JMP    FAR [ESP+4]    ; eip, cs
  212. 		RET
